<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Webcafe</title>
<style>
  body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: sans-serif;
    background: #2b2420;
    color: #e8d9c7;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 100vh;
  }
  .wrapper {
    max-width: 600px;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  .screenshot {
    width: 100%;
    height: 300px;
    background: #3a322d;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    color: #aa9a8b;
  }
  a.button {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 10px 18px;
    background: #3f2e22;
    color: #e8d9c7;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin: 12px 0;
  }
  a.button:hover {
    background: #5a4030;
  }
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
</head>

<body>
<div class="wrapper">
  <h2>Welcome to Webcafe!</h2>
  <div class="screenshot">
    <img src="/images/sc.png" alt="Screenshot of the game Webcafe.dev" style="width: 100%;height: 100%;">
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    Welcome to Webcafe. I wanted to learn real-time systems using WebSockets and this felt like the perfect playground.
    I built this from scratch to understand how proper multiplayer servers operate, how tick-based simulation works,
    and how to deliver a shared world with smooth distributed rendering.
  </div>

  <a href="/" class="button">☕ Enter the Cafe →</a>

  <div class="section">
    Tools used: Node.js, WebSockets, Three.js, Linux, Nginx, Certbot, and a self-managed Vultr VPS.
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    Built a multiplayer virtual space engine from scratch using WebSockets + Node.js + Three.js,
    deployed on a self-managed VPS with server-authoritative tick-based simulation and distributed
    client rendering supporting desktop + mobile.
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    The motivation behind this project was simple: developers tend to isolate themselves. I wanted
    to create something where people could gather in the same space and interact in real time.
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <a href="https://github.com/bculleec/webcafe.dev" style="color:#e8d9c7;">View on GitHub</a>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
